articles.author: Maya Gebeily, Laila Bassam
articles.description: The strikes came after days of bombing by Israel of Beirut suburbs considered strongholds for Hezbollah.
articles.title: Heavy strikes shake Beirut as Israel expands Lebanon campaign

articles.author: Maya Gebeily, Timour Azhari, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: An Israeli strike hit Lebanon's northern city of Tripoli for the first time early on Saturday, a Lebanese security source said, after more bombardment hit Beirut's suburbs and Israeli troops sought to make new ground incursions into southern Lebanon.
articles.title: Israeli strike hits north Lebanon as raids pummel Beirut suburbs

articles.author: Leigh Thomas
articles.description: Thousands of protesters took to the streets in several major cities around the world on Saturday to demand an end to bloodshed in Gaza, as the conflict in the Palestinian enclave approaches its first anniversary and spreads in the wider region.
articles.title: Anniversary of Gaza war draws thousands of pro-Palestinian protesters around the world

articles.author: Steven Aristil
articles.description: Haiti is reeling after the Gran Grif gang killed at least 70 people, including infants, in Pont-Sondé, and forcing over 6,000 residents to flee.
articles.title: Haitian prime minister goes abroad for support after gang massacre

articles.author: Francois Murphy
articles.description: The head of Austria's far-right Freedom Party, which won this week's parliamentary election, urged other parties on Saturday to accept that he should lead the next government and warned them against forming a "coalition of losers".
articles.title: Austrian far-right head urges rivals to let him govern after election win

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Leaders of China and North Korea on Sunday traded a vow of enhanced bilateral cooperation on the 75th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries, state news agency KCNA reported.
articles.title: China and North Korea mark 75th anniversary of ties with vows of cooperation

articles.author: Fedja Grulovic
articles.description: The country's worst floods in years follow an unprecedented summer drought.
articles.title: Rescue teams search for missing in Bosnia's floods

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Kazakhstan votes in a referendum on Sunday on whether to build its first nuclear power plant, an idea promoted by President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev's government as the Central Asian nation seeks to phase out polluting coal plants.
articles.title: Kazakhstan votes on whether to build first nuclear plant

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Islamabad is on high alert ahead of diplomatic events including a visit by India's foreign minister.
articles.title: Dozens of Pakistan police injured in clashes with supporters of former PM Khan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of Hungarians gathered outside the headquarters of the country's state television on Saturday, protesting against what they described as the government's "propaganda machine" and calling for an independent public service media.
articles.title: Thousands protest in Hungary demanding end to state media 'propaganda'
